{
  "texts": [
    "This linearity resembles biological learning and also alleviates the need for excessive model re-training (Mehta et al. 2021).",
    "The idea here is to adapt the model to new streams of data while retaining knowledge of the previous domains (Parisi et al. 2019).",
    "Using this strategy, we may pre-train models that have previously been trained on biomedical texts and expose them to clinical notes and the vocabulary associated with them.",
    "While this method is not specifically related to model compression, we can develop lightweight clinical models by using already compressed biomedical models, such as BioMobileBERT, and through continual learning adapt them to the clinical domain.",
    "We explore this approach in this work in Section 3.2."
  ]
}